<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900927-0120</DOCNO><DOCID>900927-0120.</DOCID><HL>   Par Pharmaceutical's   Quad Unit Is Barred   From Working for U.S.</HL><DATE>09/27/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   PRX</CO><IN>DRUG MANUFACTURERS (DRG)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   SPRING VALLEY, N.Y. -- Quad Pharmaceuticals Inc. wasbarred by the Defense Logistics Agency from contracting withthe federal government until Aug. 31, 1992.   The move affects Quad, based in Indianapolis, but not itsparent, Par Pharmaceutical Inc.</LP><TEXT>   Par and Quad were fined earlier this year for illegalpayments to a Food and Drug Administration official. Bothhave recalled products amid charges that they changedmanufacturing processes without following FDA requirements.The action against Quad follows a two-year investigation ofthe company.   &quot;While Quad is of course disappointed in this decision, welook forward to the time when we can demonstrate that we areresponsible to do business with the federal government,&quot; saidKenneth I. Sawyer, president of Par.</TEXT></DOC>